Local Host Resolution Protocols

- LLMNR, NBT-NS, and mDNS:
    * Microsoft and other operating systems use LLMNR and NBT-NS for local name resolution when DNS fails.
      Similarly, Apple and Linux systems use mDNS.

    * These protocols are susceptible to interception and spoofing due to their 
      unauthenticated, broadcast nature over UDP.

    * Responder and Dementor can be used to impersonate services by sending 
      forged responses to hosts querying these protocols.
